    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="330"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1663.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>When the President returned I acquainted him with the attitude of our Government
                    as per your telegrams November 26, 5 p.m., and December 2, 11 a.m. Press of
                    Horacio Vasquez now publishing articles telling the people not to believe these
                    falsehoods; that Washington never said such things; and that it is a trick to
                    deceive the country. Government convinced that revolution brewing and requests
                    me to ask what financial assistance can be expected in case of trouble.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
